\myparagraph{Question} A natural language question {{arxiv_2204_11677_FO0027||FO}} is a sequence of words expressing an interrogative intent. A question can be complete (i.e., self-contained/full-fledged/intent-explicit), or incomplete (i.e., context-dependent/partial/intent-implicit). Incomplete questions require context from previous questions and answers in the conversation to be answered correctly.